zapping: a TV viewer for the Gnome desktop
zapping:
zapping: Zapping is a TV viewer for the Gnome desktop. It runs on Linux
zapping: Icon Linux, FreeBSD Icon FreeBSD and Solaris.
zapping: 
zapping: With Zapping and a TV card you can watch TV, take screenshots,
zapping: and record video and audio. Zapping has a deinterlacer and a
zapping: Teletext viewer built in and supports Closed Caption and Teletext
zapping: subtitles. Got a remote control? Zapping supports LIRC too.
